values: ECD will soon be hit by its largest and most destructive storm in recent memory when arguably the two most recognize Goddesses wage a 1-on-1 war for the very first time. The informative "Tale of the Tape" tells all as we await this Saturday's forthcoming clash:

Throughout the countless years of semi-embellished and exaggerated ECD stories, there are extremely rare instances when even the almighty Writer fails to realize the true magnitude of certain situations. It's no secret that Diana DiBuccio and Lauren Stopa have a legitimate claim as the sport's most famed and iconic females. Their legacies are built on career longevity and incomparable success as well as the admiration and recognition of those far beyond the ECD nation. How many appearances? A "grand slam" what? If you're not sure or sold on the forthcoming DiBuccio-Stopa confrontation, let this in-depth documentation do the talking:

Every major era in ECD's colorful history has witnessed the emergence of two imposing forces that stand out from their warrior peers. The original Ocean Road Park run featured its most brutal collision when Chris Adams fought John Tronolone. During the Dark Days, the historic C. Adams-Fitzpatrick rivalry set new standards of competition and altered behind-the-scenes designs. As time went on, the dominating couples - Butler/Bertsch & Krott/Kerr - waged war in an ECD first while K. Adams and Tronolone contested for the crown at the first centennial. And in more recent times, titans K. Adams and Fitzpatrick mightily clashed on the road to 200. So it's no secret that a pair of individuals have undoubtedly remained at the top of the pecking order even before the advent of this "reunion" phase. After more than a decade of dedication and sacrifice, it's finally going to happen:
These iconic queens are the last of a dying breed as evident by their continued rise in star power, admirable physical improvements, and collapse of their female counterparts.

The Writer has announced the following reunion special set to occur on November 21, 2015 only at Wall High! Additionally, The "Championship Chase" is confirmed for the event, returning for the first time since February 2011.
Ten years of paper notes, computer files, and endless numbers have been calculated: Who is the greatest ECD player of all-time?
**Details of the extraordinary encounter are indeed coming soon!**

This post-war, "reunion era" of East Coast Dodgeball is supposed to be for the nostalgia and memories of what once was. The weapons rest in the museum and the warriors heal their numerous wounds as they await an occasional gathering for a single night of light competition and youthful fun. This DIBUCCIO v. KERR encounter? Yes, a behind-the-scenes favorite eons ago, but never written or printed in ink then .. so why now? Simple! The dinner may be over but the dessert tray is full - dig in! BACKGROUND Those privileged to experience events 1 to 200 enjoyed the heartiest of ECD meals. As documentation proves, the not-so-friendly gentlemen waged hellacious wars - Fitzpatrick vs. C. Adams, Cornero vs. Letsche, Tronolone vs. K. Adams - on the grandest stages countless different occasions. Although significantly outnumbered, the fierce females of the ECD world have indeed battled as well: Bertsch-DeCuir, Stopa against Lima, and seven remarkable Winston-only conflicts. The colorful history essentially went unfinished, until now.
DIANA DIBUCCIO is unquestionably the most recognized female star ever and arguably of all-time. Her giant personality, mental and physical on-court capabilities, and everlasting devotion and longevity kept ECD breathing beyond any measure and paved the path for all incoming talent, ladies especially. One in particular formed an immediate bond with the larger-than-life ECDElite Hall of Famer en route to establishing her own legacy. When MELISSA KERR first set foot at ECD 40, little did anyone of us realize she would become the greatest, most dominant female force in ECD history. But that's exactly what happened! A rocket arm, athletic agility, catching ability, and fearless attitude earned her the monicker "Killer Kerr", a fitting name that remains today. In 2013, she too, joined the prestigious ECDElite. With their colossal encounter looming, the Megill-Edwards, Wolf-Londono, and the aforementioned gentlemen's clashes have undoubtedly met their female counterpart. DIBUCCIO v. KERR, best friends-turned-adversaries - an ECD dessert or after-dinner drink if you will - is on 11 22. Did I mention it's a CREAMation Match?

As the ECD World prepares for the titanic DiBuccio-Kerr clash on 11 22, feast your eyes on the brief history of the CREAMation Match. Unbelievably, there have 12 of such encounters and obviously, the records don't stop there.

The East Coast Dodgeball World will be treated to a Turkey Day celebration of its own when ECD's most recognized female star collides with the biggest female weapon for the very first time ever. And in the spirit of the holiday, one will be served a great big piece of that delicious cream pie. It's DiBuccio-Kerr on 11 22.

The secret is out and yes, ECD returns on 11/22 with its second reunion of 2014 titled FEAST COAST DODGEBALL. While this year's grand meal is being secretly prepared, allow The Writer to ease your anxiety with this special history section of Thanksgiving past. Be sure to click on each event number for more past dishes!
__________________________________________________________________________________
DODGEBALL 15 | "The Road Continues" Future ECDElitist TOM ADAMS against the wildly intense KURT GASSNER, SARA DECUIR'S infamous v-shot on an unsuspecting KRISTEN DRISCOLL, an astounding 37 strong, all at the final ORP event during ECD's original run .. what didn't happen! DODGEBALL 65 | "A Thanksgiving Tradition" Held in the midst of the 2006-2007 "Dark Days", the first of three BASISTA-SMALLS matches led the action while delicious [free] pizza from nearby Luke's Pizzeria helped feed the hungry combatants in need of a special Thanksgiving meal. DODGEBALL 113 | "Wall v. All 4" The fourth installment of WALL vs. ALL was all about the native Wall "Indians" and the visiting "Pilgrims" in this bloody conflict. DODGEBALL 166 | "Megill vs. C. Adams II" In one of ECD's historic rematches, icons KEVIN MEGILL and CHRIS ADAMS waged hellacious war for the all marbles during this holiday massacre. DODGEBALL 177 | "Wall Brawl" While longtime supporters of ECD - MICHAEL EDWARDS, RYAN LETSCHE, VALERIE WINSTON, and LAUREN WINSTON - were inducted into the prestigious ECDElite Hall of Fame, the dueling armies WALL and ALL were at yet again. DODGEBALL 195 | "ThanksKilling" ECD warriors returned to the Wall Battlegrounds for the first time in four months as the most recent Thanksgiving spectacular played host to an unusual alphabetic team selection process.
__________________________________________________________________________________ Check back soon for the major announcement regarding this year's colossal attraction!

Additional Highlights & Notes ... - Crab walk opening rush and opposite throwing-arm game - Two games of classic two-team dodgeball, four games of prison ball, two games of unlimited team regeneration, and one special game of teammate regeneration via rim (courtesy Justin Wolf) Special Thanks To The Following ... - Lauren Stopa and Justin Pierce for the brand new dodgeballs - Kevin Fitzpatrick for the air pump and radio - Zach Katz and Alex Brummel for the large cooler of drinks - Gail Adams for the assortment of food - Christopher Adams who greatly helped organize this memorable event
Thanks to everyone who made our first ECD Reunion event a real success!
It's unquestionably ECD's most important time of the calendar, this year especially. What can we expect at the finale, DODGEBOWL 200, on August 10? Well, if the past is any indication, anything!
It's no secret ECD has been a wild ride. The friendships, the action, the hype, and indeed the numbers truly speak volumes .. take a look for yourself!

I was 20 when I first started this foam football-filled, 12-person gathering. An astronomical 199 events, 508 participants, and 8 full calendars later, I never thought the journey would come to this ..
The MAIN EVENT: Colossal 3 vs. 3! Six household names we've all come to befriend and respect. And in that glorious spotlight each helped create, they square off one last time: John Tronolone, Michael "Sputz", Kevin Adams vs. Kevin Fitzpatrick, Grant Cornero, Diana DiBuccio. No turning back, no tomorrow: this is your mega DODGEBOWL 200 main event. "Make A Change" For ALZHEIMER'S! ECD will give back yet again and with your help, we can really make a change. As part of Sunrise Senior Living of Wall's annual "Walk To End Alzheimer's" fund, I'm simply asking for any coins you would like to donate to help this great cause. Every penny collected will go directly to such! SMILE For the CAMERA! Trust that I only want the best and that's exactly what I hired. Founder of Michelle Amy Photography and ECD legend in her own right, Michelle Mullins, will be on hand to capture the action and excitement of the multi-hour, once-in-a-lifetime spectacle. Thank you Michelle! Winner-Take-All: RIMSHOT CONTEST The "super" centennial secondary contest will feature the return of the classic Rimshot Contest. A special prize will be awarded to the champion - good luck to all contestants! The ECDElite: FINAL CLASS I've tallied all votes and picked up the personalized awards. Five of you reading this will become members of the prestigious ECDElite Hall of Fame and I cannot express enough appreciation for your sizable contributions throughout the years. Event EXTRAS! A special artifacts table, a kick-ass musical soundtrack everyone will enjoy, and some light food and refreshments round out this stacked extravaganza.
East Coast Dodgeball greatly improved my life beyond any number, statistic, or measure. From my current and beloved occupations to the countless lifelong friendships, it has been ever-so rewarding. I believe that even in the tiniest way, it has positively affected your life as well. So for the last time, please come celebrate our tremendous accomplishment; all of us, together, have made this possible.

It was the most anxiously-awaited CREAMation encounter ever when iconic southpaw Kevin Megill clashed with blocking magician and fellow ECDElitist, Justin Wolf. Trust that on this Memorial Day Weekend '13, anything was possible. It took an extra long five-plus year stretch for this steaming rivalry to finally reach its boiling point. From the one time clash in December 2007 to last month's deadly Wall-All collision, the pair of Hall of Famers had simply had enough. The epic bout, stipulation and all, was officially announced May 14, 2013 at 11pm via ECD's Facebook page. And ever since, the ECD World buzzed at the post-match, "pie in the eye" guarantee. MEGILL v. WOLF: CREAMation 12 On paper, predicting a winner of this 12th CREAMation Rules Contest wasn't going to be easy. Even the first round, an agonizing 20-minute melee, further proved that statement true. As time passed, however, a favorite and eventual victor became more evident resulting in the sport's worst CREAMation loss in history! "Metallica Man" Megill used every ounce of strength he had remaining in that shot left arm of his to overcome his hungry, animalistic adversary. Count 'em: rounds 1 through 6 belonged solely to KMJ! Like WINNER TAKE WALL the month prior, "The Punter" Wolf managed to momentarily swing the momentum back to his side, grabbing the crucial 7th game and two of the next three. That last-ditch effort just wasn't meant to be .. From there, the Megill-led coalition bombarded their never-say-die enemies into oblivion to seal the deal on this barbaric massacre. Megill: 1-6, 8, 11-15 (12) Wolf: 7, 9, 10 (3) STATISTICAL SIGNIFICANCE MAYN EVENT was the 198th Tronolone-produced ECD event. MAYN EVENT became the fifth straight event to feature 11 or more individual games, an impressive streak that began at OCTOBERFEST in October 2012. Additionally, Prison Ball was played throughout the entire duration this 198th spectacular. In an ECD rarity, MAYN EVENT was recorded as the 38th Wet War, a first since CALL OF DUTY in July 2012. Prerna Sinha became the newest ECD acquisition at player #508; the total attendance was ten (10). The 12-3 final score was the sixth worst loss in the ECD's almost eight-year history. The 9-point deficit forced upon Wolf was the largest margin of victory in a CREAMation match ever. Captains Records Kevin Megill captured his 8th match ever, tied for the second most number of victories along with John Tronolone and Chris Adams. Megill holds the better win-loss percentage than both Tronolone and Adams at 73% (8-2-1). Justin Wolf competed in his 8th contest, extending his record-holding streak for most consecutive one-on-one matches. He left MAYN EVENT with a 2-5-1 record.
______________________________________________________________________
ECD #199 | June 29, 2013 It's the penultimate ECD spectacular and promise you won't want to miss this. DODGEBOWL 200 | August 10, 2013 No turning back, no tomorrow. This Is It as the tagline suggests; our last ride, the grand finale, one heartfelt goodbye. The emotionally-charged final chapter in the storied history of ECD. Please, please, do not miss out. Special start time for DB200 is 5pm.

I've Got QUESTIONS, You've Got ANSWERS! It's been an enduring, physical struggle the last half decade-plus. So brace yourself for an equally-challenging mental test during ECD's pre-match attraction Trivia Contest - only at ECD's 7th birthday party! Luck Has It: SEVEN RAFFLE! A mystery prize package is up for grabs and it may just have your name on it! The Numerical Pinnacle: WHO'S #500? ECD needs just three more - who, if anyone, will become the unprecedented 500th Player? "THE BIG ONE": Six-Person Showdown! Every great court general has risen high above the occasion to capture the coveted victory. For those brave and fortunate souls, bragging rights for life indeed. But it remains that only an elite few have done so on the grandest, most crucial stage of all. The magnificently star-studded, three-vs-three encounter at SEVEN is a rare, once-in-a-lifetime chance for those who have yet to taste such sweet triumph. Undeniably, SEVEN will host "The Big One" as six of the game's most recognized figures - MILLS, AVAKIAN, JACOBS, SMALLS, OBERTO, TURNER - are carefully divided into two formidible squads, each with one goal in mind. Travis MILLS Former two-time season finale headliner "Maniac" Mills has virtually done it all, with just this one exception. His comedic, good-humored antics have yet to bring him that figurative trophy; will he be able to contain his contagious laugh long enough to grab the career-enhancing win?
  • ECD Player #23
  • Debut: DODGEBALL DAY 2 | September 4, 2005
  • Notable Contest(s): Defeated at DODGEBALL XL versus Joey Kelly; also fought to a draw at DODGEBALL 150's "Battle of the Sexes" three-vs-three confrontation
  • Captains Record: 0-2-1. Joey SMALLS His showcases against Sascha Basista throughout the years were as memorable as they were hurtful. Unfortunately for this fun-loving legend, the accurately nicknamed "Eddie Gordo" remains without that prized brass ring. SEVEN is perhaps his final opportunity and bet that he will stop at nothing to attain it.
  • ECD Player #218
  • Debut: DODGEBALL 65 | November 26, 2006
  • Notable Contest(s): Defeated at FAMILY AFFAIR III (2010) versus Sascha Basista
  • Captains Record: 1-4-0. Kenny JACOBS He's the resident newbie who quickly ascended the rungs of ECD's ladder. In his almost two-year journey, the all-around athletic all-star Jacobs earned a spot in the FAMILY AFFAIR spotlight in 2011, though his victory-seeking quest was ultimately denied. At SEVEN, his second go-around amidst the familiar atmosphere might just be his crowning achievement.
  • ECD Player #462
  • Debut: 5 YEAR ANNIVERSARY (175) | September 11, 2010
  • Notable Contest(s): Defeated at FAMILY AFFAIR IV (2011) versus Bobby Vetrano
  • Record: 0-1-0. Rob AVAKIAN This rare, but certainly appreciated appearance at SEVEN couldn't be any more crucial for the formerly-known "Trenchcoat". While Avakian holds the most match victories amongst his captains counterparts, none of which have come at such a high-profile event. Will his unpredictable, offensive strategy lead him to the career defining moment he's yearned?
  • ECD Player #60
  • Debut: DODGEBALL 8 | October 22, 2005
  • Notable Contest(s): Defeated in "The War To Settle The Scores", three-vs-three war at DODGEBALL CXV
  • Record: 2-3-0. Dan TURNER One of ECD's most controversial figures in all of its illustrious history. Orginally slated as one-half of the THREE YEAR ANNIVERSARY's main attraction eons ago, Turner, for reasons unknown, no-showed the historic event! This wouldn't be the first time he pulled the disappearance act either, a dubious legacy still conversed about to this very day. There is absolutely no question that this Pond Scum icon is indeed the "wild card" in SEVEN.
  • ECD Player #117
  • Debut: DODGEBALL XXVIII | February 25, 2006
  • Notable Contest(s): SEVEN will be his first big-time main event
  • Record: 1-1-1. Kelly OBERTO This chick means business. Guaranteed, her ultra-athletic background will be unleashed for the ECD community to witness and it won't be pretty. Arguably the most well-rounded competitor of the SEVEN cast, her lone defeat at the hands of ECDElitist Diana DiBuccio in July '11 will only add fuel to the fire.
  • ECD Player #356
  • Debut: DODGEBALL 119 | December 29, 2007
  • Notable Contest(s): SEVEN will be her first big-time main event
  • Record: 0-1-0.
    ________________________________________________________________ We've Done It, Again. And Luck Had Nothing To Do With It. SEVEN Magical Years Are Ours. SEVEN: THE ANNIVERSARY September 1, 2012 | 5:30PM Ocean Road Park

The Writer has done it again. Well-over 100 familiar faces and moments compiled into this magical musical showcase. From the casual fan to the weekly diehards, this is for you - thanks to all for making it possible.
Six of the game's biggest names carefully selected into this one gigantic encounter. The reason? Quite simple actually: each have never captured "the big one". But before such great detail is unveiled, let's find out just who will occupy the coveted spots at SEVEN: The Anniversary:

It was destined to occur at some point during this journey. Now is finally the time where the single, biggest powerhouses perhaps of all-time clash in this epic, earth-shattering confrontation. And you will never, ever see it again. Kevin Adams v. Kevin Fitzpatrick at East Coast Dodgeball CLASH of the TITANS on 08.04.2012. Here's their incredible story over a half-decade in the making ..
_______________________________________________
5, A.D.: Fifteen year-old Kevin Adams joins the ECD universe becoming the third of the four recognized brothers to enter the games. 10, A.D.: In just his fifth outing, the young Adams squares off against sibling Steve in the first-ever season finale extravaganza. 12, A.D.: Kevin Fitzpatrick makes an immediate impact in his debut, battling the aggressive nature of C. Adams, Pierce, and most notably, "The Creation" Tronolone. 19, A.D.: Fitzpatrick impressively vanquishes Katz in his inaugural showdown. 20, A.D.: Perhaps in a prelude to their future clash, both Adams and Fitzpatrick receive prestigious "Excellence Awards" - Act Of Courage and Powerhouse Thrower, respectively. Clearly, their god-like statuses were beginning to increase. 35, A.D. Tension had finally boiled over when Fitzpatrick went toe-to-toe with Tronolone in their first of two intense meetings. 48, A.D.: Adams becomes the 6th Captains Champion defeating female sensation DeCuir. 49, A.D. Adams retains the coveted championship, eliminating the maniacal Tronolone from contention. 50, A.D.: In the grandest clash of the unforgettable era, Adams and brother Steve turn back the challenge of the "other brothers" duo, Tom and Chris. Meanwhile, Fitzpatrick becomes the second Act Of Courage recipient. 51, A.D.: Adams' reign of generalship supremacy continues with his record-tying fourth consecutive victory, this time over the gifted Letsche. 52, A.D.: The Captains Championship is subsequently retired following the Adams-Letsche sequel. 62, A.D.: In an unprecedented feat, Fitzpatrick captures three Battle Royal victories further cementing a legacy early in his career. 70, A.D.: In unquestionably one of the most satanic melees ever witnessed, the rivalry that revolutionized the captains match comes to a head when Fitzpatrick rather handily defeats C. Adams to conclude the calendar. 76, A.D.: Legend Lauren Stopa is stopped dead in her tracks by Fitzpatrick in a crushing 11-1 slaughter. 81, A.D.: Tronolone and Herrera are soundly sent packing against the tandem of Adams and V. Winston in the ECD World's first CREAMation Rules encounter. 86, A.D.: In his next war, Adams successfully battles the athletically-blessed Cornero in a contest billed as "2005 v. 2007". 94, A.D.: Adams puts on a heroic clinic despite his captain's denied quest at grabbing hold the event victory. The Writer believes this event to be a pivotal turning point in the career of the now 17 year-young warrior. 100, A.D.: To some, it is still the grandest and greatest of all-time and maybe for one prime reason: the triumphant trio of Pierce, Edwards, and Adams faced off against Tronolone, Letsche, and Fitzpatrick. To date, it is the only time in any ECD era where Adams and Fitzpatrick met in any type of captains confrontation. Additionally, some ECD historians and the omniscient Writer strongly believe that this event placed Adams atop the ECD throne. 105, A.D.: In the midst of this period of transition, Fitzpatrick and C. Adams wage war in their long-awaited return bout from the previous calendar in just the third CREAMation Rules collision. 111, A.D.: Not to be outdone, Adams once again turns back Cornero in their own sophomore encounter. 115, A.D.: Fitzpatrick finally closes the coffin on his enduring feud with C. Adams in this classic three-vs-three war also featuring Londono, Marzarella, Basista, and Avakian. 120, A.D.: After being voted by his peers, Adams reigns supreme as the "Player of the Year". 123, A.D.: Herrera is no match for the powerful Fitzpatrick in this anticipated special attraction. 142, A.D.: Fitzpatrick adds another trophy to his collection, winning his 4th Battle Royal. To this day, he holds the record for the second-most number of Battle Royal titles. 145, A.D.: Adams however had his own record-shattering agenda by destroying high-ranking general Edwards in a 6-0 blow-out. The victory made Adams the only captain to reach both 5 straight and 9 total wins. 169, A.D.: Christmas was never quite the same after this contest when Fitzpatrick hands friend-turned-foe Wolf a brutal season beating. 171, A.D.: Fitzpatrick and Tronolone meet only once more, this time to the distinct advantage of Fitzpatrick. The win sent Tronolone packing for nearly 19 months. 174, A.D.: In his final captains war to date, Adams, alongside icon Megill, mightily clashed with long-standing, revenge-filled rivals C. Adams and Tronolone. Fitzpatrick, an uncommon ally of the C. Adams-Tronolone coalition, was rather instrumental preventing Adams his own closure. 175, A.D.: Both Adams and Fitzpatrick are inducted as charter members of the ECDElite Hall of Fame. 184, A.D.: Fitzpatrick - along with the elder Winston and Pierce - compete in a memorable "Star" War with renewed rival C. Adams, familiar enemy Edwards, and the cunning youngest Winston. The all-knowing Writer trusts the figurative ECD crown belonged solely to Fitzpatrick; a lengthy, year-long stretch [and beyond]. 189, A.D.: Earth-shaking rumblings begin of the never-before-seen, one-on-one clash of titans between Adams and Fitzpatrick. 191, A.D.: The announcement of the mega Adams-Fitzpatrick encounter is made official for 192, A.D. 192, A.D.: And so it goes .. the coined CLASH OF THE TITANS is carved in stone to host the massive, titanic battle between arguably the two most powerful, imposing forces in all the heavens.
_______________________________________________
Adams and Fitzpatrick might just be the very last of their kind. The decline of iconic figures Tronolone and Megill as well as the permanent departure of one C. Adams have dispelled any re-emerging notions of the formerly-known "Big Three". The grounds' security system has also experienced its members dwindle leaving Pierce as the sole survivor. Major leaders like Wolf, Stopa, Edwards, Katz, among several others remain as high-ranking officials, but with slightly less experience than their counterparts. Adams and Fitzpatrick have clearly etched their names in the annals of time and perhaps this one, last effort is all that's left to prove. Through all the mental anguish, physical pain, and in rare cases emotional breakdown, they have each - at one period or another - undeniably ascended to the pinnacle of ECD. But at CLASH OF THE TITANS, only one will be able to plant their flag on Mount Olympus. There isn't anything more to say or do for the power rests in the bodies, minds, hearts, and souls of the two gods that remain.
Kevin Adams vs. Kevin Fitzpatrick CLASH OF THE TITANS | 192 A.D. August 4, 2012

12th WALL Army History has shown these never-say-die homeland defenders don't necessarily need the numbers; the wealth of experience and firepower has sent their invaders packing more often than not. Past squad leaders - Fitzpatrick, Pierce, Wolf, Adams, Katz, among others - are extremely well-versed on their own home turf. If the same familiar faces reunite on Friday the 13th, there's no halting what the 12th WALL Army can and will overcome. 12th ALL Army Despite the swarming number of soldiers on the battlefield, somehow the invading fleet has embarrassedly retreated a whopping 7 out of 11 attempts! Oddly enough, ALL, like their counterparts, certainly has the wherewithal and knowledge in legends Megill, Stopa, Teitelbaum, Jacobs, Tronolone, and Edwards. But with some of their most valuable assets not at 100%, a new, sound strategy might just be the answer they're seeking. Time will indeed tell for the massive 12th ALL coalition as both their bodies and weapons need to be fully prepped for the war that awaits.
